reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good reliable AA batteries, but not inexpensive
reviews.reviewText: There are 12 sealed packs of 4 each in the box, and the batteries look well sealed too. Each is marked with a "2033" expiration date on the bottom. I checked one package with my multimeter, and they're putting out 1.65 volts, so starting exactly where a new AA battery should be.These appear to be good, long-lasting, and reliable batteries, but perhaps overpriced. Amazon Basics alkaline batteries, also with a 10-year shelf life, are at well under half the price of these, for a package of 48. I hope these unknown brand batteries will be worth the premium battery price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars As good as any others I've tried
reviews.reviewText: These are a great value when on sale or have coupon offers - for example today they are $23 but have a $6.89 Amazon instant coupon, so about $16 for 48 AA batteries.I find these to be just as good as any other brand I've tried here. While I cannot speak to shelf-life yet, the battery life is excellent. I've tested them in things like LED candles and flashlights and they do great. In fact, I've kept them in a couple of LED candles running non-stop 24/7 for the past 29 days and they only started to slightly dim at around day 20 (but are still running and lit enough to consider acceptable at 29 days).For normal use (in other words - not leaving them running non-stop for a month as I did in my test) I can tell the battery life will be great.
